			<h4 style="color: var(--blue)">Contrastive Alignment</h4>
			<p>CLAP trains two encoders (one for text, one for audio) to project their inputs into a shared vector space. The objective is geometric: matched (audio, caption) pairs should land near each other, mismatched pairs far apart. The text encoder gives the audio embedding a vocabulary; once aligned, you can query audio with sentences and vice versa, even for categories the model has never been explicitly trained to classify.</p>
		</div>
