			</svg>
		</div>
		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--orange)">Batch Negatives</h4>
			<p>Contrastive learning needs negative examples (pairs that should be pushed apart) and CLAP gets them for free: every other item in the batch is treated as a negative for any given positive. A batch of <em>N</em> pairs yields <em>N</em> positives along the diagonal and <em>N(N&minus;1)</em> negatives off-diagonal. This is why contrastive methods benefit so much from large batch sizes; more batch members means harder negatives, which means stronger gradient.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

