		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--teal)">Masked Acoustic Modeling</h4>
			<p>MERT borrows the recipe from BERT (text) and HuBERT (speech): randomly mask spans of input frames, then ask a Transformer encoder to reconstruct what was hidden from surrounding context. No labels, no captions, just the audio. The bet is that to fill in a missing chunk of music, the network must implicitly model harmony, rhythm, and timbre, which makes the resulting features useful for downstream tasks like pitch detection or genre classification.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="concept-row">
		<div class="concept-figure">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 100 72" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
